Unfriendly, in fact, prices are often directly proportional to the level of friendliness. If you can’t tell the difference, then more expensive products are usually less user-friendly than cheaper ones. These so-called “entry-level” products are actually just industrial waste.
They have very low strength; when the ball hits the racket, the vibrations are extremely intense. Hard balls can’t withstand them, and even experienced players find it difficult to control them.
The logic and subtext behind this is: Tennis is such a difficult sport that we knew you wouldn’t be able to learn how to play it, and we also knew you wouldn’t be willing to spend a lot of money on a good racket. So we offered a cheap one to trick you into buying it. After
