Actually, there are many considerations when it comes to the clothing and styling for girls who are slightly overweight.
Girls who are a bit plumper should not wear skirts that are too short or too long; the length should be around the knees, just enough to cover the areas of their thighs where they are slightly thicker.
If a skirt is too short, it will reveal the fat on the legs.
If it’s too long, it can give the impression of someone being short and chubby.
If you wear clothes that are divided into upper, middle, and lower sections, it will make you appear taller naturally. Using different colors for the upper body, skirt, and stockings will create an effect that makes you look slimmer.
In fact, many dark-colored clothes are a staple for slightly plump girls (something the author can well understand), and dark colors are also an excellent way to conceal a fuller figure. Elegant and sophisticated black skirts are also a top choice for slightly plump girls.
Wearing dark-colored clothes, especially a black skirt, can make you appear slimmer.
If your calves are quite thick, try not to wear socks and shoes that draw too much attention to them.
The more popular it is, the better. Also, the colors shouldn’t be too bright.
To avoid giving the impression of being overweight when people focus on your legs and feet.
For slightly plumper girls, it’s really important to teach them the tricks of how to dress well and match clothes properly.
Chubby girls should definitely avoid wearing tight-fitting short skirts. Additionally, tops should not be too short or tucked into the skirt, as this can make people feel uncomfortable. If you have thicker legs, it’s best to wear black or mesh stockings (the kind with a fine pattern). Choose a soft, printed fl
Of course, even slightly plump girls have their own considerations when it comes to wearing short skirts.
A chubby girl wearing a short skirt should choose a top that matches the color of the skirt, as this will create an illusion that makes her plump figure appear taller.
A short skirt paired with high heels can make your legs look longer and slimmer, which is definitely the most trendy combination for summer!
If you are a girl with a fuller upper body but slimmer legs, I recommend choosing a glamorous one-piece skirt.
It not only covers up your big belly, but also highlights your best features.
A-line skirts can really make you look slimmer and are more suitable for girls who are a bit plumper. For the top, choose something a bit tighter to create a layered look, which will also help you appear thinner.
A simple white T-shirt paired with a short skirt – even plump girls can try it.
Even slightly plump girls can also look stylish when they dress appropriately.
As long as one can master the rules of dressing and matching, even slightly plump girls can become the center of attention.
Now that I’ve made changes to my clothing style, I also need to exercise more in my daily life and strive to get rid of the label of being a slightly overweight girl as soon as possible 😄
