Over the past few years, Credit Suisse has continuously conducted comprehensive and diverse financial literacy activities targeting young people, including college students. By collaborating with top domestic universities and organizing innovative practice competitions, the company has subtly guided the consumption needs of this group, helping them develop a rational approach to spending, plan their financial choices wisely
As Double Twelve approaches, Joy Credit reminds all consumers to establish a reasonable consumption mindset and a correct view of money, to resist impulsive and excessive spending, and to avoid misconceptions related to consumer loans, in order to protect their personal credit and future financial well-being.
When consuming, it is essential to plan in advance and repay within your means on time.
If overdue, the overdue record will be recorded in the personal credit report, which may have an adverse effect on future financial activities such as buying a car or a house.
At the same time, when enjoying financial products and services, one should also choose legitimate institutions and channels, and pay attention to verifying whether the relevant institutions possess the necessary qualifications to operate.
In the future, Joyoung will, as always, rely on its mature and reliable consumer finance system as well as continuously updated financial products to provide consumers with more tailored and diversified services. It will continue to help the public improve their financial knowledge, foster the concept of rational consumption and moderate borrowing, and become a trusted
