It’s too much attention; wherever I go, everyone is looking at me, which is really uncomfortable! (Actually, it’s kind of cool in a way.)
The fuel cost for a 1-kilometer journey is around RM1 (and the car owner doesn’t care about it at all).
You should practice the posture for getting in and out of the vehicle; otherwise, it might be a bit awkward (because you might not be able to get out of the cabin and get stuck halfway).
The engine noise is so loud that you’ll go deaf as soon as you get out of the car. (But it’s still really exciting!)
The car is too large; it would be very cramped if parked in a regular parking space. I’m really worried about getting hit by the door of the car next to me when it opens!
It’s a bit lonely because there are no competitors on the road (that’s what the editor said; it has nothing to do with the car owners, haha).
