Let the spirit of the university resonate in harmony with the spirit of the times – Xinhua News Agency
The so-called “university spirit” refers to a series of educational philosophies and value pursuits that have been gradually accumulated over a long period in the development of a university; it represents the very essence of that institution.
From ancient times to the present, the spirit of universities has been of paramount importance for the development of politics, economy, culture, technology, society, and even the progress of a nation as a whole.
Since the birth of the world’s first modern university, universities have undertaken a unique mission that sets them apart from other social organizations. For universities in our country, which emerged during times of national crisis, their spirit has been deeply influenced by traditional culture and the changes of the times. They advocate for the values of “cult
Currently, with the trends of informatization and internationalization in higher education becoming increasingly evident, and global competition in education, technology, and talent intensifying, higher education, as an important “supply-side” factor, is facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges in its structural reforms.
In particular, with the introduction of the "Comprehensive Plan for Promoting the Development of World-Class Universities and Disciplines," it not only showcases our country’s confidence and determination in transitioning from a major player in higher education to a powerhouse in this field, but also sets higher and more stringent requirements for the development of
How can we strive to join the ranks of the world's top institutions in a relatively short period of time, and on the basis of existing gaps, accelerate the establishment of several world-class universities and a number of world-class disciplines, thereby achieving a “overtake on the curve”?
In addition to having firm confidence in their goals, paths, and capabilities, universities should also fully leverage three key advantages: firstly, the advantage of being latecomers, by continuously attracting outstanding academic talents from abroad and learning from the advanced experiences of world-class universities, they can achieve significant improvements in academic standards and educational quality
It is particularly important to realize that building world-class universities cannot mean that all universities should look the same. While each university should leverage its strengths, it must also showcase its individuality and characteristics.
The distinctive features of a school should not only possess common Chinese characteristics but also reflect each school's unique goals, educational traditions, and resource endowments.
In the case of Zhejiang University, we focus on highlighting three distinctive aspects in our educational approach: First, we emphasize the cultivation of innovative and entrepreneurial talents by creating an integrated educational environment that combines science and education with industry-university collaboration, thereby forming a comprehensive entrepreneurial education ecosystem. Second, we emphasize the importance of
In this process, it is particularly important to always uphold the university spirit and ensure that it resonates in harmony with the spirit of the times.
For Zhejiang University, the motto of “Seeking Truth and Innovation,” along with the shared values of “Diligent Study, Moral Cultivation, Clear Discrimination, and Sincerity,” and the mission statement of “Embracing Diversity, Promoting Truth and Virtue, Leading the People Forward,
This is an important guarantee for the school to adhere to the correct direction of education, continuously accumulate cultural depth, and unite spiritual strength. It is rich in connotation and holds profound significance.
Among these, “Haina Jianghe” emphasizes the spirit of openness and inclusiveness, reflecting the ambition to utilize the talents from all over the world by adopting the high-quality educational philosophies of world-renowned universities; “Qizhen Houde” highlights the pursuit of truth and virtue, suggesting that universities should not
This series of spiritual concepts and value pursuits is precisely the soul of Zhejiang University’s 120-year history of education.
“The wise hear what is silent; the discerning perceive what has yet to take form.”
Chinese universities should further base themselves on the overall situation of the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics, deeply grasp the historical context and mission of higher education, and accelerate their development into world-class universities.
At the same time, by upholding humanistic care and independence, we enable the spirit of the university to interact with the spirit of the times and the national ethos. This interaction creates an inexhaustible force that contributes to the prosperity of the nation and the rejuvenation of the nation, as well as to the realization
