The maximum duration for Guangxi college students to take a break from studies to start a business is 5 years – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, May 19th (Reporter Zhang Ying) Reporters have recently learned from the Education Department of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region that in the future, colleges and universities in Guangxi will implement a flexible academic system, extending the leave of absence period for college students.
To promote the enhancement of entrepreneurial and innovative capabilities among college students, departments such as education and human resources in Guangxi have collaborated to establish entrepreneurship platforms, including more off-campus practice teaching bases, university science and technology parks, college student entrepreneurship parks, and entrepreneurship incubation centers, providing external support for college students' entrepreneurial endeavors
According to the requirements, by 2020, the area of innovation and entrepreneurship practice bases in undergraduate colleges and universities should reach over 3,000 square meters, while those in higher vocational schools should reach over 2,000 square meters.
The government encourages universities to establish innovation and entrepreneurship credits, and gives priority to supporting students who perform exceptionally well in innovation and entrepreneurship practices to change their majors.
University teachers are required to spend at least two months every two years working in industry or enterprises as part of their professional development, in order to enhance their awareness and capabilities in innovation and entrepreneurship education.
The Education Department of the Autonomous Region requires all colleges and universities in Guangxi to thoroughly implement the innovation and entrepreneurship training programs for college students, striving to ensure that every college student participates in such a program during their time at school.
Colleges and universities should actively organize students to participate in various innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels, and provide financial support for them.
