Professor Nakamura’s invention has not only completely transformed the lighting industry but also led to the development of white light-emitting diodes (LEDs) that are now widely used in everyday life and industrial production, making a tremendous contribution to the well-being of humanity.
When reading out the praise for Li Lanjuan, Sun Yifeng stated that as a pioneer in China’s artificial liver technology, Professor Li Lanjuan developed a unique and effective artificial liver system. This system has led to significant breakthroughs in the treatment of severe hepatitis and liver failure, significantly reducing the mortality rate associated with
In the battle against COVID-19, the “Four Resistances and Two Balances” strategy proposed by her and her team, along with the three key technologies of artificial liver, microecology, and stem cells they brought, significantly improved the survival rate of patients in critical condition.
When reading out the praise for Li Xiaoliang, Sun Yifeng stated that Professor Li Xiaoliang laid the foundation for innovative research in operations management, shaped the way of thinking in supply chain theory and practice, and completely transformed business models around the world.
Li Xiaoliang is famous for popularizing the concept of the “whip effect” in operations management and has explored measures to address this phenomenon.
Today, amidst pandemics and tense economic situations, the bullwhip effect is becoming increasingly prominent, causing severe disruptions in supply chains.
Li Xiaoliang’s forward-thinking research provides much-needed assistance in times of difficulty, helping the industry overcome challenges and thereby bringing tremendous social value.
When Sun Yifeng read out the praise from Zhu Lilan, she mentioned that in her scientific research work, she discovered a breakthrough and innovative staining technique for sample preparation, which has earned her a high reputation among her peers in the scientific community both domestically and internationally.
With her extraordinary scientific and technological achievements, she was honored with important titles such as Academician of the International Eurasian Academy of Sciences, earning her a rightful and esteemed position among the world’s leading figures in the field of science and technology.
Chen Xin, the acting director of the Australian Macao Chinese Medicine Research Institute, read out the commendation speech for Professor Chen Kaixian. He stated that Professor Chen Kaixian has been engaged in drug research and development for over 40 years. His outstanding scientific achievements, as well as his significant contributions
His active role in promoting the development of traditional Chinese medicine in Macau and the Greater Bay Area fully reflects his sense of mission in contributing to the country’s medical development strategy.
In his speech reading out the commendation from Dean Su Chengzhong, it was mentioned that Ms. Jiang Chaohui’s participation in the research and development led to over 15 significant inventions and patents, which are related to storage virtualization, navigation, file systems, and power management. These inventions and patents
As a highly accomplished inventor, Ms. Jiang is often able to simplify complex technologies and theories, making them accessible to the general public.
Finally, Chen Kaixian delivered the thank-you speech on behalf of the honorary doctors.
He is very pleased to see that the pharmaceutical industry in Macau and the Greater Bay Area has set a good example: from the establishment of the first National Key Laboratory for Traditional Chinese Medicine Quality Research at the University of Macau to the vigorous development of traditional Chinese medicine in the region, the University of Macau has played
Furthermore, he believes that the management team at the Australian National University possesses foresight and vision. They not only provide an excellent academic environment for students to conduct research but also contribute to society by nurturing many responsible individuals.
He is honored to be able to engage in exchanges and cooperation with ANU and sincerely congratulates ANU on the achievements it has made in recent years.
