As NFTs rapidly gain popularity, a new concept has emerged within the crypto community.
In 2021, a blockchain game called Axie Infinity had a huge impact in Southeast Asia. Some residents who lost their jobs due to the pandemic began to earn a stable income from playing this game.
“Axie Infinity” is a pet-raising game based on blockchain technology, incorporating various gameplay elements including NFTs. It is currently the NFT project with the highest transaction volume, having surpassed $3 billion to date.
According to TokenTerminal data, Axie Infinity’s daily revenue exceeded $8.2 million, coming close to that of “Honor of Kings”.
On August 6th of this year, Axie Infinity officially announced that its daily active users had exceeded 1 million.
The popularity of Axie Infinity has introduced a new “play-to-earn” model to a wider audience. With the help of blockchain and smart contracts, players are no longer just passive characters within the game. In addition to enjoying the gameplay and earning financial rewards, they can also participate in the governance of the game’s
This sense of agency is not granted by the game developers, but is ensured by blockchain technology.
