In September 2020, Mr. Lu learned about a factory building located in Zhangting Town, Yuyao, Zhejiang through a real estate agency. After several on-site inspections, Mr. Lu decided to purchase the factory building.
In December of the same year, after discussing the details of purchasing the factory building with Mr. Lin, a family member of the property owner, Mr. Lu transferred 200,000 yuan as a deposit through bank transfer on the same day.
Mr. Lin signed as the recipient on the “Deposit Receipt for the Sale of the Factory Building.” The receipt stipulates that “if the buyer does not wish to purchase the factory building, the deposit shall belong to the seller; if the seller is unwilling to sell the factory building, the deposit will be returned to the
However, subsequently the parties were unable to reach an agreement on key contract terms such as the scope of the factory building sale and the payment method, which led to a delay in signing the property sales contract.
Considering that the two parties failed to reach an agreement on the contract terms, a few days later, Mr. Lin returned the 200,000 yuan deposit to Mr. Lu.
After much effort, Mr. Lu found a house he liked, paid the deposit, and had all the necessary funds ready to complete the purchase. All that was left was to sign the contract, but then the seller decided not to sell the house anymore, leaving Mr. Lu feeling both helpless and angry.
For this reason, Mr. Lu filed a lawsuit against Mr. Lin in the People's Court of Yuyao City.
After trial, the court found that the failure of both parties to sign a formal contract could not be solely attributed to the defendant. It was reasonably inferred that the negotiations were unsuccessful. Hence, the deposit penalty clause should not apply in this case, and the defendant is not liable for the breach of contract involving the double return
After the first-instance judgment, the plaintiff filed an appeal.
Recently, the appellate court upheld the original judgment.
[Lawyer’s Reminder] It is essential to exercise due diligence during the transaction process.
When signing a contract, as the buyer, it is essential to fulfill the necessary duty of care. This involves verifying information such as the property owner's details and whether the property is occupied by anyone else. It is also important to clearly specify the exact time and place of delivery in the contract to prevent any disputes that may
Following the conclusion of the “Democracy Summit” on Friday, a spokesperson for China’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs stated on Saturday (December 11) that the United States’ hosting of the “Leadership in Democracy Summit” was an attempt to “draw ideological lines, instrumentalize and weaponize democracy, carry out
The Chinese government believes that for a long time, the United States has imposed its political system and values on others, promoted “democratic transformation,” arbitrarily imposed unilateral sanctions, and instigated “color revolutions,” resulting in catastrophic consequences.
“Democracy” has long become a “weapon of mass destruction” for the United States to use in its interference with other countries.
This summit is an action taken by Biden to fulfill his campaign promises.
The two-day conference was held via video, with leaders from 111 countries around the world invited to attend, including those from Taiwan. However, China and Russia were not invited.
On the eve of the summit, China and Russia criticized the United States for its own democratic issues, stating that the US did not have the qualifications to host such a summit.
There are also doubts both internationally and within the United States. For example, some have criticized that among the invited participants were leaders with authoritarian tendencies, such as those from the Philippines, Poland, and Brazil. Some suspect that the true intention of the Biden administration in organizing this summit was not to promote democracy but rather to achieve
The newly appointed German Chancellor Olaf Scholz also participated in the Video Democracy Summit.
A statement issued by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs on Saturday stated, “Today, the pathological aspects of American democracy are evident, with issues such as money politics, identity politics, partisan antagonism, political polarization, social divisions, racial tensions, and the widening gap between the rich and the poor intensifying.” It added
U.S. President Joe Biden stated in his speech, “As leaders of the government, it is our responsibility to listen to our citizens, strengthen the safeguards of democracy, promote reforms, and achieve transparent and accountable governance. This will help us better withstand the forces of authoritarianism and those who seek power at the expense of
He emphasized that democracy is not something to be taken for granted. “We must constantly renew it with each new generation, and in my view, this is the decisive challenge of our time.”
Biden also said that as global democracy and human rights face persistent and concerning challenges, democracy needs defenders.
The United States has pledged that following this Democratic Summit, a one-year initiative will be launched, including a fund of $424.4 million, aimed at strengthening democracy around the world and providing support to independent news media.
The United States hopes that all countries will make specific and public commitments to improve their democratic systems before the physical Democracy Summit scheduled to take place at the end of 2022.
Biden said, “Let’s make sure all our countries fulfill their commitments and report on the progress we’ve made next year.”
