Education News: Beijing reduces the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools in 2016 - Xinhua Net
On the 21st and 22nd, the assessment for students with special talents entering junior high schools in Beijing was organized and implemented uniformly by the education commissions of each district.
This year, all districts in Beijing have reduced the proportion of students admitted based on their special talents, making the competition for these spots even more intense.
Taking Dongcheng District as an example, this year the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools from primary schools in this district does not exceed 5% of the total district's enrollment plan. The planned enrollment number is 380 students, and the proportion of students who actually attend junior high school does
All students who possess talents in sports, arts, or technology and have registered online are eligible to participate in the special talent recruitment assessment.
To facilitate students to participate in the assessments nearby, Dongcheng District has continued with last year's examination arrangement, setting up 1 to 2 examination locations in each school district, for a total of 13 examination locations.
The examination venues are divided according to the examination regions, with time periods set on an hourly basis. On the day of the exam, students will enter the designated examination venues in their respective regions at the scheduled times to take the tests.
On May 23rd, the District Education Admissions and Examinations Center published the list of students who passed the assessment online. Students can check their assessment results online.
