Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 11 (Reporters Dong Ruifeng, Gu Tiancheng) The Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council recently issued a notice on strengthening the prevention and control of COVID-19 in port cities. It requires that individuals leaving land border port cities (
According to the notification, the time frame for the aforementioned requirements is from the date when each province, autonomous region, and municipality determines the scope of port cities and announces it, until March 15, 2022.
In addition, the notification also proposes that port cities with the necessary conditions may study the establishment of buffer zones for epidemic prevention and control within their jurisdictions.
A responsible official from the Disease Prevention and Control Bureau of the National Health Commission stated that for some port cities, cross-border trade is a major economic pillar, with frequent exchanges between residents on both sides of the border.
By implementing a differentiated management policy based on zoning, we have transitioned from having just one line of defense against the spread of the virus to having two lines of defense. This approach is expected to move the focus of prevention and control further forward, thereby reducing the risk of the outbreak spreading. The goal is to achieve the
Recently, several local clustered outbreaks have occurred in our country, all of which were imported from overseas epidemics through port cities.
The aforementioned notice pointed out that these issues have been exposed, including untimely epidemic monitoring and early warning in some areas, failure to implement closed-loop management for personnel in high-risk positions, perfunctory regular nucleic acid testing, inadequate disinfection at all stages of the cold chain, non-standard management of centralized
The notification requires efforts in nine areas, including improving the epidemic prevention and control mechanisms in port cities, enhancing the epidemic monitoring and early warning systems, and implementing border control measures. The goal is to quickly address the shortcomings and weaknesses in these cities' prevention and control capabilities. We must maintain a relentless, scientific, and precise
The notification emphasizes that port cities should conduct simultaneous research and deployment of both epidemic prevention and control measures and the protection of people’s livelihoods. They should make hotlines for livelihood support readily accessible to the public, regularly monitor potential issues related to the supply and prices of basic necessities, and promptly address and proactively respond to
According to the notice, the port cities referred to include the counties (cities, districts, banners) where the open land, water, and air ports are located, as well as the cities (prefectures, leagues) and municipalities directly under the Central Government where these ports are situated. The specific scope will be determined
