I came across the following article by chance, which discusses from both a commercial and a storage (shelf-life) perspective why this client preferred to use a logistics company located in a bonded area to handle the canning process. Although canning is considered a form of advanced processing and falls outside the scope of services provided by bonded
I visited many manufacturers of milk powder and got in touch with their production lines.
In fact, the raw materials for both bagged and canned powdered milk are exactly the same; there is no difference between them at all.
So, everyone must be wondering: Why is the shelf life of bagged products one year, while that of canned or bottled products two years or even longer?
Or another question: Why is there such a big price difference between canned and bagged products?
In fact, from this perspective, many consumers, or those in the motherhood group, believe that the quality is much better because the raw materials used are different.
Actually, the raw materials are the same; it’s just that people think the more expensive ones are better.
Some consumers, with this mindset, have reported that the taste or texture of canned products is indeed different after consumption!
Now, let me first explain to you the reasons why canned food is expensive. What exactly makes it so costly?
If their raw materials are the same, why is there such a big difference in price?
Because when manufacturers set prices, they generally take into account that if the price for bagged products is too high, consumers will find it difficult to accept. This means that the profits generated by the manufacturers would be very low, or even non-existent. So, how can manufacturers survive in such a situation?
Therefore, they have implemented a significant increase in the pricing of their canned products to ensure their profit margin.
Therefore, most manufacturers primarily promote canned products rather than bagged ones.
Moreover, the manufacturers that you're referring to spend tens of millions, or even hundreds of millions, on annual advertising expenses. Where does all this money come from?
As you can all imagine…
As society develops, market promotion expenses also continue to increase. This includes costs for promotional staff in shopping malls, display costs for products, expenses for offering free gifts with products, and advertising expenses, among others.
Therefore, various manufacturers are also constantly introducing new products, which come in canned or bottled form, and their prices are also continuously rising. In fact, this is a result of the increase in market costs.
The main purpose is to obtain higher profits; in fact, the increased cost of their raw materials will not exceed 3 or 4 yuan at most.
There are also some brands that, in order to promote their products, will stop at nothing and establish connections with doctors in hospitals, asking them to assist with the promotion of those products in exchange for commissions ranging from 30 to 80 yuan per product sold.
And China's relevant laws absolutely do not permit such practices; in fact, this kind of behavior is harming consumers.
It is recommended that everyone, if they already have jars at home, buy bagged powdered milk and transfer it into those jars. This can save money while also improving the preservation and sealing of the powdered milk, with no adverse effects on children.
Also, please don’t assume that canned products have a longer shelf life than bagged products. Once opened, the shelf life of both canned and bagged products remains the same; it’s just that bagged products are more difficult to store afterward and are more prone to becoming damp and deteriorating.
