Wang Zhun, the secretary-general of the Provincial Tea Industry Association, said happily that current factors such as the pandemic are more or less affecting the tea market, but judging from the situation at the Tea Expo, there were many highlights.
Xinhua black tea, with its distinctive red hue, has been infused with the essence of tea culture. It has become highly popular and generated brisk trade, as the Hunan tea industry welcomes a new spring.
