The cover plate on the microfluidic chip is made of PC material; please do not introduce solvents that can react chemically with PC.
Do not use a syringe to inject the sample directly into the chip, as this may easily cause liquid leakage.
Before shipment, all microfluidic chips with ordinary substrates are tested with pure water at an injection pressure of 500 mbar (for channel depths of 100 μm) or 300 mbar (for channel depths of 50 μm).
All glass substrate chips are tested with pure water at an injection pressure of 800 mbar (for 100 μm channels) before shipment. During use of these glass substrate chips, please be cautious not to collide them with sharp objects, as this may cause damage to the substrate.
During use, please consider the viscosity of the solution and do not exceed this range; otherwise, leakage may occur.
For microfluidic microchips with a common substrate, when using a syringe pump for pure water injection, we recommend setting the flow rate below 150 μL/min. For the oil phase, we suggest setting the flow rate below 50 μL/min.
Please take into account the actual viscosity of the injected liquid, and gradually increase the value of your flow rate parameter from slow to fast.
After completing the experiments with the general-purpose chip, please clean the internal channels promptly to avoid blockages.
Microfluidic chips are considered consumables and cannot be reused repeatedly over a long period of time.
No refunds or exchanges will be provided if the chip is damaged due to long-term use or improper operation.
If you need a microfluidic chip that can withstand higher pressures or flow rates, please contact customer service for customization.
The normal delivery cycle for these chips is within 1 week. For items in stock, delivery can be made within 24 hours after placement of the order. Please consult with customer service before placing your order.
