If you plan to enter this industry, you can choose to find a place for training. However, if you don’t have such intentions, it’s best to learn on your own. After all, training is quite expensive and it will take you six months to complete.
But if you plan to get involved in this industry, training is indeed a very good choice, especially for those with weak self-control.
If you have a strong sense of self-control, you can also choose to study on your own, but it will probably be more exhausting.
Of course, choosing a good training institution is a very important matter.
First and foremost, it is essential to consider the teaching staff of the institution. If the teaching staff is not strong enough, then the training institution loses its significance. Of course, some newly established training institutions may not have particularly strong teaching staff.
Secondly, before making a choice, it’s advisable to conduct some research on the training institution. It would be best to learn about the students who have graduated from this institution, as only they can truly provide insights into the quality of the institution and the courses offered.
Hello, actually, I don’t know how to answer your question either, because you haven’t provided any information about your own situation, and learning something is closely related to an individual’s own circumstances.
For example, your major, age, the language you want to learn, and even the city you live in – all these factors are related to the industry you plan to study or work in.
If you are a student who has not yet graduated, or if you are a computer science graduate, then I personally recommend self-study if you have enough time. This is the most efficient and cost-effective approach. There are many excellent training institutions available both offline and online nowadays, but they tend to be expensive and require
But if it's the situations I mentioned, self-study would be very convenient. There are many free learning resources available online nowadays, and there are also plenty of training materials on Bilibili. If you don't know how to find these resources, you can contact me through the introduction provided to get free resources or
In addition, there are some other classic books that can be combined with videos for comprehensive learning.
If you are not majoring in computer science but are still willing to invest the necessary money and time in learning, it is recommended that you enroll in a training institution. This approach makes the learning process less demanding, as instructors provide detailed explanations, and there are always people available to answer any questions you may have. Additionally
Moreover, nowadays many training institutions sign employment agreements and offer internal referral opportunities. After completing the training, students are recommended for jobs at companies, which can save a lot of time during the subsequent job interview process.
The above are some of my views. Since I didn’t know much about your situation, my explanation was only general and not detailed. If you have any other questions, you can contact me at any time for further discussion.
