Yunnan: Coordinating and Standardizing the Management of Public Welfare Positions in Rural Areas – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Kunming, December 12 (Reporter Lin Bifeng) In order to continue providing employment assistance to those who have been lifted out of poverty and to consolidate and expand the achievements of poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province has recently introduced relevant policies regarding the management of public welfare positions
According to a relevant official from the Yunnan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security, to date, Yunnan has established a total of 448,300 public welfare jobs in rural areas, aimed at providing employment for individuals who have been lifted out of poverty and other disadvantaged rural groups.
These new regulations were jointly issued by seven departments in Yunnan, including the Human Resources and Social Security Department, Rural Revitalization Department, and Finance Department. They mainly standardize aspects such as the scope of candidates for grassroots recruitment to rural public welfare positions, fund management, position development, and position management.
In terms of job development and setting, the new regulations specify that the establishment of positions should be carried out in accordance with the principles of “establishing positions based on needs, assigning personnel to positions, dynamic management, and total quantity control”; “the person who develops the position is responsible for using it”; as well as
The recruitment process must be carried out in accordance with the steps of announcement, application submission, review, public disclosure, employment, pre-job training, and assignment to a position.
In addition, the new regulations also clarify the specific responsibilities of the departments responsible for developing rural public welfare positions, as well as the subsidy standards and methods for these positions. It is stipulated that each department responsible for developing rural public welfare positions must purchase commercial insurance for accidental injuries for the employees assigned to these positions; relevant
