What is abnormal public opinion?
Randomly select six trending searches from the same event, presenting them in the forms of [isolated peak], [zigzag], and [cliff].
The “Island Peak” pattern involves artificial boosting of popularity, allowing a topic to quickly rise on the trending lists and attract widespread public attention. The “Sawtooth” pattern uses periodic increases in popularity to ensure the topic remains on the trending lists for an extended period. Once the topic has fulfilled its purpose,
In Figure 9, the peak of popularity for one event coincides precisely with the trough of another event, down to the very second. This must indicate that a group of coordinated “water army” members were given a task to launch a new round of attacks.
The professionalism of black PR is evident in this case: dozens of trending topics make it onto the list simultaneously. These topics are carefully selected to either attract attention, provide scientific information, stir up controversy, divert attention, influence perception, mislead judgment, arouse emotions, or influence decision-making. The accounts belonging to these
Communication is a science. By setting aside all subjective factors such as opinions and emotions and focusing solely on objective data, even unethical or negative public relations tactics will have no place to hide.
Every step taken leaves a trace, and we dig those traces out together.
