Address: 156 Huancheng South Road, Happiness Home, 12th Floor
It all started with a friend’s recommendation; out of trust, I decided to give it a try. My initial budget was 70,000 yuan for basic renovations.
As soon as they entered the store, a series of scams began.
This was my first time visiting the store. I just showed them my floor plan, and they didn’t even measure the house on-site. Yet, they were able to give me a quote stating that they could sell my 135-square-meter house for 70,000 yuan. They briefly showed
Their second trick is that as soon as you arrive at the store, they will try to persuade you to pay the deposit. Once you pay that money, you will never be able to get it back, unless you have enough experience to argue with them effectively.
While I was hesitating about whether to pay the deposit, they would invite their so-called manager to come and tell me that if I paid the deposit today, I would be entitled to a certain discount.
This is a big scam; I’m a living example of someone who was deceived. In a moment of impulsiveness, I paid a deposit of over ten thousand yuan.
The quote he gave me has many issues; the amount of 70,000 yuan does not include the costs for plumbing and electrical renovations, nor does it cover any doors, cabinets, or the bathroom. Yet these three aspects are precisely what make up the bulk of the basic installation costs.
Apart from these issues, the fees they charge for their service points are also higher than those of other companies.
I have lost trust in this company; they made me sign the contract without explaining anything clearly to me at the beginning.
When I went to ask them for a refund, they acted as if they were very experienced, and there was even a dedicated team set up to deal with such situations.
In any case, they would insist that it was the customer’s problem and that they were completely blameless.
There are all sorts of excuses for shirking responsibility, and there are many other details as well that I don’t want to mention one by one; just thinking about them makes me want to cry. In short, don’t choose them. My friend who hired them to renovate her house also experienced poor quality work
What a rip-off! Those things were originally just fake, deceptive decorations designed to deceive people. Now they’ve been “rebranded” as something supposedly beautiful, but it seems the company went bankrupt again, and then they changed the design yet again.
So everyone, please don’t choose such a deceptive and unreliable renovation company.
In the future, when making choices, everyone should make more use of Baidu to search for relevant information and seek advice, as home renovation is not a small investment after all.
