From the past to the present, I have always opposed any form of slander and abuse, and I certainly cannot accept such personal attacks.
In civilized societies, we should be able to tolerate everything, but we must put an end to such villains.
If we set aside political parties and factions, the first thing we need to resist is this kind of uncivilized behavior.
Since you started by sending me a Facebook friend request, then proceeded to make sarcastic posts, and later even attempted to post what you claimed were the location of my home and my father’s name on social media, I have chosen to remain unresponsive from then on.
Later on, not only did you continue to tag me even more frequently than before (six times a day), but you also went on to discuss me in rather explicit and humiliating ways on Facebook with your so-called friends. Comments about my appearance, figure, fertility, and even things like “planting strawberries in bed”
Later on, I received messages from several friends regarding a photo of me uploaded to their Facebook profiles, along with comments that contained elements of sexual harassment.
I’m sorry, but as a girl, I can no longer remain silent any longer.
After the news of my reporting to the police was uploaded, you didn’t show any sign of changing your behavior at all; instead, you became even more arrogant.
I don’t care what your political background is, nor do I care about your social status; in our society, it is essential that both genders be respected.
Yes, you can continue with these sarcastic, humiliating, and abusive remarks. You can also keep saying that you’re just showing concern for me. You can continue to believe that this isn’t harassment, and you might even continue to deny that you made those images, or continue to post all kinds of offensive statements.
That’s right; I can’t, and I don’t have the ability to stop you.
I neither know you nor do I want to know you. Moreover, your comments on my appearance and figure are completely unnecessary.
I don’t even think there would be a single girl who would agree to let someone humiliate her in such a way just to gain fame.
A friend asked me, "Are you okay?"
Even if I say yes, you still won’t believe me.
I don’t think there would be a single girl who, after being bullied in such a way, could still say that she’s okay.
Whether in the workplace, society, politics, or business, only those who lack even basic morals would choose to harm any woman in such a manner.
I believe that fairness resides in people's hearts.
I’ve excerpted some of the comments for everyone to review and discuss.
Since you posted it yourself, no one can impersonate you, right?
I can only say that you are the public enemy of civilization.
A knowing smile
Vietnam People’s Newspaper Website – Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Minh Chinh attended the third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprises Development Forum
During the third Vietnam National Digital Technology Enterprise Development Forum, two main conferences were held, with discussions revolving around two key themes: the role of digital technology enterprises in the country’s digital transformation, and their contribution to economic recovery and development both during and after the COVID-19 pandemic.
The Minister of Communications and Media, Nguyen Meng Hung, stated that in 2021, despite the ongoing spread of the COVID-19 pandemic, the number of digital technology companies in Vietnam and their revenue still maintained growth momentum, reaching nearly 10%.
In 2021, Vietnam made significant progress in the development of digital products, focusing on solving the major challenges the country faced. Many of these digital products have been exported abroad, and as a result, Vietnam’s ranking in digital technology has improved.
Minister Nguyen Mengxiong called on digital technology companies to take responsibility for developing the country’s digital transformation platforms, stating that undertaking this task is equivalent to fulfilling a national mission.
At the forum, leaders from various departments and state agencies, along with enterprises, organizations, and individuals involved in the research, development, application, and transfer of digital technologies, shared innovative ideas and solutions for mobilizing and pooling resources from across society to support the growth of Vietnamese technology companies and jointly drive the country’s digital
During his speech at the forum, Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that digital transformation is an inevitable path for the world and an objective requirement for development.
Digital transformation has become a global issue that benefits everyone; therefore, it is necessary to mobilize the entire population to participate.
People and businesses are the core, main body, goals, and driving forces of digital transformation.
Therefore, all policies must be aimed at serving the people and businesses.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that digital transformation needs to reflect the national spirit and should be driven primarily by internal forces, with strategy, long-term vision, and decisive factors being key. External forces, however, can also serve as important catalysts and breakthrough points.
He also believes that digital transformation needs to drive both in-depth development and sustainable development. It should contribute to the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pandemic, economic recovery and development, adaptation to subsequent changes, and the overcoming of natural resource depletion. Furthermore, it should support the transition towards a green economy by promoting
Digital transformation requires participation in the establishment of databases that protect and promote a country's cultural values, historical traditions, and local customs, as well as driving the digital transformation in sectors such as banking, taxation, land management and development, and logistics.
The ultimate goal of digital transformation is to make people happier and ensure the continuous prosperity and development of the country.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng has called on governments at all levels, various agencies, and enterprises to intensify leadership and guidance in the development of digital technologies, enhance awareness of digital transformation, continue to establish and improve institutional frameworks for digital transformation, and promote the development of digital technology enterprises with a spirit of respect, communication
During the forum, Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh attended the award ceremony for the 2021 “Made in Vietnam” Excellent Digital Products Awards and the opening ceremony of the “Made in Vietnam” Digital Products Exhibition.
