“The ‘Wisdom Gathering in Hunan’ 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opens - Rolling News - Hunan Daily Online - Huasheng Online”
Hunan Daily, December 10th (All-media journalist Zhou Zhiheng) On the 9th, the “Intelligent Talent Summit for China’s International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry – 2021” opened in Zhuzhou.
Wang Cheng, a member of the Standing Committee of the Provincial Party Committee and Minister of the Provincial Party Committee Organization Department, attended the launching ceremony and delivered a speech.
Wang Cheng pointed out that hosting a talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress, demonstrating Hunan’s sincere commitment to valuing, seeking, and making effective use of talent.
Hunan boasts an excellent tradition of recognizing, valuing, and respecting talent, along with a broad platform to support talent development and favorable environmental conditions for achieving a better quality of life. In recent years, the province has vigorously implemented a talent-led development strategy. Guided by the Furong Talent Action Plan, it has
Currently, Hunan is fully implementing the strategic positioning and mission of “Three Highs and Four New Initiatives.” It will further broaden its efforts to attract talented individuals, introduce more favorable policies to support innovation and entrepreneurship, and concentrate more resources to create better conditions. Hunan looks forward to the collective wisdom and efforts of
The event site included exhibition halls for Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, and the Hunan Free Trade Pilot Zone. The Provincial Department of Science and Technology, the Provincial Department of Industry and Information Technology, and the Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security released key lists of technological innovation needs for the advanced
Forty-eight large enterprises, including CRRC, Zoomlion, and Yuanda Technology, recruited talents on-site. Nearly a thousand recent graduates from relevant fields and professionals from the community participated in the talent matchmaking programs.
