The main stream of the Yangtze River has achieved full coverage of green comprehensive service areas on the water surface – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Wuhan, December 11 (Reporter Wang Xian) The Fuling Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area in Chongqing was completed and put into operation on the 10th as scheduled. This is the second water-based green comprehensive service area to be officially operational in the upper
To date, the Water Green Comprehensive Service Area has covered the upper, middle, and lower reaches of the Yangtze River.
Qiu Jianhua, deputy director of the Yangtze River Navigation Administration under the Ministry of Transport, stated that previously, provinces including Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, and Jiangsu had established and operated 10 green, integrated service areas along the middle and lower reaches of the
The full coverage of green comprehensive service areas on the water represents another milestone in the construction of green shipping on the Yangtze River, with the capacity of the Yangtze River to handle ship-generated pollutants and provide shipping services having been significantly enhanced.
According to the information provided, the Water Green Comprehensive Service Area is an important facility that offers a full range of production and living services to ships and their crew members, helping to address their urgent, difficult, and pressing needs.
The two newly established and operational green comprehensive service areas on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River integrate living services, production services, and government services. Centered around the theme of environmental protection and featuring ship maintenance and emergency rescue services, these areas enable ships berthing at the port to receive multiple services in one stop
Three American aircraft carriers assembled near China’s borders; one of the most powerful weapons in the U.S. military made a rare visit to Guam. January 17, 2022. Pro-China media reported: The latest satellite images show three American aircraft carriers gathering near China. American media also revealed that one
According to the Chinese think tank “South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness Platform,” on January 9, satellites detected the U.S. aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson in the vicinity of the Balabac Strait.
The Balabac Strait connects the South China Sea with the Sulu Sea and is a strategically important location on the first island chain of the Western Pacific Ocean.
The platform anticipates that the USS Carl Vinson will be deployed to the South China Sea.
This is the first time that the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson has deployed F-35C fighter jets and CMV-22 Osprey amphibious transport aircraft.
In addition to the USS Carl Vinson, there is also the USS Abraham Lincoln, which set sail from the United States on January 3rd, currently operating in the upper Pacific Ocean.
The USS Lincoln also deployed for the first time an F-35C carrier-based aircraft squadron, which is part of the 314th Fighter Attack Squadron of the United States Marine Corps.
In addition to the two aircraft carriers mentioned above, the U.S. Navy currently has another carrier deployed in the Asia-Pacific region: the USS Ronald Reagan, which is stationed in Yokosuka, Japan.
The aircraft carrier battle group also includes the USS Lake Champlain missile cruiser, the USS Stockdale missile destroyer, among others.
On January 17, 2022, the “South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness Platform” released the latest satellite images, showing three U.S. aircraft carriers gathering in the vicinity of China.
(Weibo @South China Sea Strategic Situation Awareness) Three US aircraft carriers assembled near China; the most powerful weapons made a rare visit to Guam. On January 17, 2022, the flight route of the US Marine Corps’ transport aircraft CMV-22B was as follows.
(Weibo @SouthChinaSeaStrategicSituationAwareness) According to a report by CNN on January 17th, one of the most powerful weapons in the U.S. Navy’s arsenal made a rare visit to Guam over the weekend.
The Ohio-class nuclear submarine USS Nevada, equipped with 20 Trident ballistic missiles and dozens of nuclear warheads, entered the U.S. Navy base in Guam last Saturday (January 15th).
The deployment of three U.S. aircraft carriers near China, along with the rare visit of their most powerful weapons to Guam, is seen by analysts as a signal to both allies and enemies in the increasingly tense situation in the Indo-Pacific region.
This is the first time a U.S. ballistic missile submarine has visited Guam since 2016, and it is also the second public visit to Guam since the 1980s.
Three U.S. aircraft carriers deployed near China; the most powerful weapons made a rare visit to Guam. In recent years, China has built a large number of military facilities in the South China Sea.
The image shows Yongshu Island in the South China Sea, which belongs to China.
(US Navy statement) The visit of the Ohio-class nuclear submarine Nevada to Guam strengthened cooperation between the United States and its allies in the region, demonstrating the US’s capabilities, flexibility, combat readiness, and ongoing commitment to the security and stability of the Indo-Pacific area.
Ballistic missile submarines are commonly referred to as “Boomer submarines”.
The whereabouts of the 14 Thresher submarines in the U.S. Navy fleet are usually kept strictly confidential.
The secrecy surrounding ballistic missile submarines has made them the “most important component of the nuclear triad” in terms of survivability. This triad also includes ballistic missiles launched from silos on U.S. soil, as well as bombers such as the B-2 and B-52 that are capable of carrying nuclear
While chatting with friends about Meta’s recent 26% drop and a $251 billion loss in market value, Zuckerberg responded that the company is “facing unprecedented competition.” What could be the reasons for this?
Meta (formerly Facebook) is essentially an advertising company, with its revenue primarily coming from advertisements. In today’s world, profitable advertising companies usually have their own traffic channels.
Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and so on—regardless of their functional positioning—are all traffic channels for Meta.
Not only that, but Meta is also the largest advertising network. Many apps integrate Meta’s advertising services, and it is through Meta’s advertising platform that these apps generate revenue.
But times have changed.
Firstly, due to the adjustments in Apple’s privacy policy, it has become very difficult for Meta to obtain user data, which has affected the efficiency of ad placement.
Apple’s current privacy policy is user-friendly, clearly informing users whether apps are allowed to access their information, and the natural reaction of most people would certainly be to deny such access.
If Google manages to cause further damage in the future, the impact on Meta’s revenue will be even greater.
Secondly, the role of China in Meta’s past revenue growth has also weakened (although the exact proportion of this factor is uncertain, its impact was indeed present).
Everyone generally knows that Meta doesn’t have any operations in China, but this understanding is not entirely accurate.
Every year, Meta derives at least 10% of its revenue from China, with the majority of this coming from Chinese companies engaged in overseas business operations.
Meta has several hundred employees in its office in Hong Kong, as well as several major agents on the Chinese mainland.
For Chinese companies seeking to expand into overseas markets, Meta remains an unavoidable advertising channel, with a significant portion of the advertising expenditure going to Meta.
Interestingly, while ByteDance’s platform is now one of Meta’s main competitors, Meta managed to make a considerable amount of money from ByteDance in the previous two years.
Various domestic agencies are helping ByteDance with advertising on Meta, and Meta’s performance in the Greater China region is also very good.
I haven’t specifically looked into it recently, but it certainly won’t be any better than before.
The phase in which Chinese companies were spending large amounts of money overseas has passed.
Thirdly, the expansion of new traffic channels has not been successful.
Facebook is getting older and older, and new platforms, including TT, are no longer under Meta’s control.
The biggest problem is not just the decline in income, but the lack of expectations for growth.
The capital market doesn’t only focus on income; what’s more important is the outlook for the future.
It’s quite obvious that Meta’s expectations were not sufficient.
In order to tell a new story to the market, Zuckerberg talked about the “metaverse.”
The metaverse is indeed one of the potential directions for the future, but its implementation cycle is relatively long. The progress made in this area over the next two or three years should not be sufficient to support Meta’s current market value.
So, the next two years should be a relatively tough period for Meta.
Despite Facebook’s current success and annual revenues of $100 to $200 billion, it is actually in a state of significant crisis. Compared to other internet companies and high-tech firms, it lacks any effective protective barriers to safeguard itself from potential threats.
Although several of his social media apps, such as Facebook and WhatsApp, currently have high daily active users and are considered mainstream platforms, Facebook doesn’t have much confidence in the face of TikTok’s rapid development. Disruption could happen in the blink of an eye.
Given that the concept of the metaverse, while promising, remains unattainable and has no chance of success in the short term, Facebook is in a very dangerous position. This is also the fundamental reason why Zuckerberg keeps changing the company’s name and constantly seeks new directions. However, I believe his choices are wrong
Article 17: The state implements a registration and practice management system for the qualifications of registered fire engineers.
Individuals who have obtained the qualification certificates for Level 1 or Level 2 Certified Fire Engineers can practice in the name of a Certified Fire Engineer at the corresponding level, as authorized by the registration authority.
Article 18: The Fire Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security is the registration and approval authority for Level 1 Certified Fire Engineer qualifications.
The fire protection agencies of the public security organs in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the Central Government are the registration and approval departments for Level 2 Certified Fire Engineers, and they are also responsible for the preliminary review process for the registration of Level 1 Certified Fire Engineers.
Article 19: Individuals who have obtained the qualification certificates for Level 1 or Level 2 Certified Fire Engineers and wish to register must be employed by an approved fire technology service organization or a key unit for fire safety. They shall submit their registration application materials to the fire department of the public security authorities at the location
Article 20: Upon receiving the registration application materials from the applicant, if the materials are incomplete or do not conform to the statutory requirements, the fire protection authorities of the provincial, autonomous regional, or municipal public security organs shall inform the applicant in person or within 5 working days of all the necessary corrections. If
For both accepted and rejected registration applications, a written certificate bearing the official seal of the fire protection agency of the local public security authorities and the date of issuance shall be provided.
Article 21: The fire protection agencies of the public security departments at the provincial, autonomous region, and municipal levels shall, within 20 working days from the date of receiving the registration application, complete the preliminary review of the application materials for the qualification of a Level 1 registered fire engineer and the registration approval
The Fire and Rescue Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security shall make a decision on whether to approve the application within 20 working days from the date of receiving the application materials and preliminary review opinions submitted by the fire agencies of the provincial public security organs.
If a decision of approval cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the applicant shall be informed of the extended period and the reasons therefor.
For decisions denying approval, the reasons shall be stated in writing, and the applicant shall be informed of their right to apply for administrative reconsideration or to initiate an administrative lawsuit in accordance with the law.
Article 22: The registration approval department shall issue and deliver the registration certificate at the corresponding level within 10 working days from the date of making the approval decision.
Article 23: The validity period of each registration certificate is 3 years.
The registration certificate serves as the professional credential for a registered fire engineer at the corresponding level during its validity period and shall be kept and used by the registered fire engineer himself/herself.
Article 24: Those applying for initial registration shall submit their applications within one year from the date of obtaining the qualification certificate for a Level 1 or Level 2 registered fire engineer.
When applying for initial registration after the deadline, the requirements for continuing education stipulated in these regulations must be met.
The specific procedures for initial registration, renewal of registration, change of registration, cancellation of registration, and refusal of registration shall be separately stipulated by the Ministry of Public Security.
Article 25: Continuing education is a prerequisite for registered fire engineers to renew their registration, re-register, and for those who need to re-initiate registration after the expiration of the initial registration period.
During each valid registration period, fire engineers registered at all levels shall complete the corresponding continuing education as stipulated.
Article 26: The registration and approval authorities shall promptly announce to the public the relevant information regarding the registration of certified fire engineers, establish a credit file for these professionals, and implement a credit management system for their practice activities.
Article 27: The registration management departments responsible for the qualifications of fire engineers at all levels shall strictly enforce the relevant provisions of the 'Administrative Licensing Law of the People's Republic of China'.
That’s all for today’s exam information sharing. I hope it can be of some help to everyone.
Everyone must work hard to prepare for the exam and strive to pass the Fire Engineer examination as soon as possible!
