The joint medical exercise “Peace Rescue-2021” between the Chinese and Vietnamese armed forces has been successfully concluded – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Hanoi, December 12 (Zhou Na, Teng Huaijin) On the morning of December 12, all Chinese units participating in the Sino-Vietnamese military joint exercise “Peace Rescue-2021” returned safely to Guangxi, China,
During this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese militaries focused on the significant topic of humanitarian medical rescue, closely adhering to the mission of providing medical care and saving lives. They completed various tasks such as joint medical command, on-site rescue operations, and the treatment of a large number of wounded personnel according to practical combat
The results of the exercise were affirmed by both the Chinese and Vietnamese militaries.
At the closing ceremony of the exercise, Ruan Xiongsheng, the director of the Vietnamese Exercise Steering Committee, deputy director of the General Logistics Department of the Vietnamese People’s Army, and chief of staff, said that through this exercise, Vietnamese medical personnel learned about exercise organization and professional activities from their Chinese counterparts
The results achieved through the exercise demonstrated the professional capabilities of the military medical forces from both countries in terms of medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control.
Chen Chunming, head of the Chinese Guidance and Coordination Group and Deputy Director of the Health Bureau of the Logistics Support Department of the Central Military Commission, stated that this exercise is another innovative and pioneering effort built upon the successful joint medical consultation activities held in 2018, and it holds great significance as
During the exercise, the Chinese People’s Liberation Army donated medical protective masks, medical protective clothing, rapid nucleic acid testing equipment, and other health and epidemic prevention supplies to the Vietnamese People’s Army.
